<li id="cite_note-zero-8">^ <a href="#cite_ref-zero_8-0"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-zero_8-1"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> These are only distinguished from the Ø (zero) reflexes of <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ḥ/</span> and <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/ʻ/</span> by <span title="Representation in the International Phonetic Alphabet (IPA)" class="IPA">/e/</span>-coloring the adjacent vowel *a, e.g. PS <i>*<span class="Unicode">ˈbaʻ(a)l-um</span></i> ('owner, lord') → Akk. <i>bēlu(m)</i> (<a href="#CITEREFDolgopolsky1999">Dolgopolsky 1999</a>, p.&#160;35).</li>
