<td>conventional penalty</td>
<td>Hurrian</td>
<td><i>uriḫull-</i></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Akkadian was also a source of borrowing to other languages, above all <a href="/wiki/Sumerian_language" title="Sumerian language">Sumerian</a>. Some examples are: Sumerian <i>da-ri</i> ('lastingly', from Akkadian <i>dāru</i>), Sumerian <i>ra gaba</i> ('riders, messenger', from Akkadian <i>rākibu</i>).</p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Akkadian_language&amp;action=edit&amp;section=35" title="Edit section: Example text">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Example_text">Example text</span></h2>
<p>The following text is the 7th section of the <a href="/wiki/Code_of_Hammurabi" title="Code of Hammurabi">Hammurabi code</a> , possibly written in the 18th century BC.</p>
